    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Group of flowering plants containing around 55 genera and 2000-4000 species located primarily in warm or tropical regions, especially Southeast Asia and Brazil. Most are aromatic evergreen trees or shrubs.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
